activityName: treatment of waste paperboard, unsorted, sorting
includedActivitiesStart: The activity starts with "waste paperboard, unsorted" being available to the sorting facility.
includedActivitiesEnd: The activity ends with "waste paperboard, unsorted" being sorted and "waste paperboard, sorted" available for transportation at the gate of the sorting facility.
ISICSection: E - Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities
generalComment: This activity represents the treatment of 1 kg waste paperboard (cardboard) from separate collection, i.e. a source-segregated municipal solid waste fraction, through sorting for recycling. The activity starts with receiving the unsorted waste paperboard, as collected from the households, at the sorting facility and ends when sorted fractions are produced.
